The `instanceof LanguageModelToolResultPart` check was always returning false for `LanguageModelToolResultPart2` instances, causing tool results to be processed incorrectly in the type converters.

## Problem

When implementing a chat language model provider that supports tool calling, the type converter functions `LanguageModelChatMessage.from()` and `LanguageModelChatMessage2.from()` use `instanceof` checks to determine how to process message content parts:

```typescript
// In LanguageModelChatMessage.from()
if (c instanceof types.LanguageModelToolResultPart) {
    return { type: 'tool_result', toolCallId: c.callId, ... };
}

// In LanguageModelChatMessage2.from() 
if ((c instanceof types.LanguageModelToolResultPart2) || (c instanceof types.LanguageModelToolResultPart)) {
    return { type: 'tool_result', toolCallId: c.callId, ... };
}
```

However, `LanguageModelToolResultPart2` instances would fail the `instanceof LanguageModelToolResultPart` check because the classes had no inheritance relationship, despite being conceptually related.

## Solution

Changed `LanguageModelToolResultPart2` to extend `LanguageModelToolResultPart` instead of just implementing the interface:

```typescript
// Before
export class LanguageModelToolResultPart2 implements vscode.LanguageModelToolResultPart2 {
    callId: string;
    content: (LanguageModelTextPart | LanguageModelPromptTsxPart | LanguageModelDataPart | unknown)[];
    // ...
}

// After  
export class LanguageModelToolResultPart2 extends LanguageModelToolResultPart implements vscode.LanguageModelToolResultPart2 {
    declare content: (LanguageModelTextPart | LanguageModelPromptTsxPart | LanguageModelDataPart | unknown)[];

    constructor(callId: string, content: ..., isError?: boolean) {
        super(callId, content, isError);
        this.content = content;
    }
}
```

This ensures that `LanguageModelToolResultPart2` instances properly return `true` for `instanceof LanguageModelToolResultPart` checks, allowing them to be correctly processed as tool results rather than falling back to text processing.

Fixes #264122.

